\f1\b\fs45 \cf0 Marketing Mix: 4Ps with 4Cs (Explained)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0\fs27 \cf3 The marketing mix is a blend of marketing variables that determine the level of marketing efforts on the target market. 4P\'92s and 7P\'92s of the marketing mix are \'96 People, Product, Price, Promotion, Place, Process and Physical Evidence. 4C\'92s \'96 Customer, Cost, Convenience, Communication; fit marketing mix perfectly.\
The marketing mix is the mixture of controllable marketing variables that the firm uses to influence and pursue the sought level of sales in the target market.\
It is the tools use to influence or persuade the wants, needs, and demands of the customer for PSI (product, service, or information).\
In simple terms; the marketing mix is the tool that is used to influence the target market and its demand for product, service, or information.\
Usually; the marketing mix describes the combination of the 4 inputs which constitute the core of a company\'92s marketing system: the product, the price structure the promotional activities, and the distribution system.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 What are the 4P\'92s of Marketing Mix? (Explained)\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 4p\'92s and 7p\'92s of the marketing mix are;\
\
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\fi-360\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0
\ls3\ilvl0\cf3 1.	Product.\
2.	Price.\
3.	Place.\
4.	Promotion.\
5.	Place.\
6.	Process.\
7.	Physical Evidence.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0
\cf3 What these Marketing Mix Ps indicate? Let\'92s Explain;\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Product\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 The product is something like good, service, information, etc. that satisfies the wants of a company\'92s target market.\
Products must follow a logical product lifecycle and marketers or producers need to understand and plan for the stages of the product lifecycle and their core challenges.\
The product must answer some questions, for example, what problem the product will solve, is the consumer or customer needs the product, and/or what will be the components of the product?\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Price\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 Price means the number of dollar customers or consumers must pay to obtain/use the product. It is the amount paid by the customer to a business.\
For example, a bottle of Wine that may cost $100.\
Prices set by the business depend on the business policy those it may be adjusted through discounts, allowances, and/or credit terms.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Place\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 Place indicates the company activities that ensure a product or service available to target consumers.\
It includes all activities like distribution channels, logistics, transportation, and locations offered by the company.\uc0\u8232 A company may have many stores offering its products across the United States, but there may still locations where customers or consumers will not access that company\'92s products.\
This is a great loss for the company. So that it must ensure that products are available to target customers or consumers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Promotion\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 Promotion refers to the activities that communicate the merits of the product to target customers and influence to buy it.\
One of the major factors of promotion for products or services is advertising.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 People\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 Indicates the employees representing the company. They interact with clients or customers for various purposes.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Process\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 The process is the procedures, mechanisms, and flow of activities by which the service is delivered to the clients/ customers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs42 \cf3 Physical Evidence\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf3 Physical evidence refers to the area or space where the company representatives will interact with the customer. It works as a tool for reassuring our customers.\
For example, a company might have impressive buildings, a well-trained staff, great website. Considerations include furniture, signage, and layout.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\sa200\partightenfactor0

