\b\fs42 \cf0 Step 1: Understanding The Marketplace And Customer Needs And Wants\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf0 It is important to understand customer needs, wants and demands in order to build want- satisfying market offerings and building value-laden customer relationships. This increases long-term customer equity for the firm.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs36 \cf0 Needs \'96 States of felt deprivation\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf0 They include the physical need for basic necessities like food, clothing, shelter, warmth, safety and individual needs for knowledge and self-expression. These need\'a7_cannot be created by the marketers as they are a basic part of human markup.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs36 \cf0 Wants \'96 The forms human needs take as shaped by culture and individual personality.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf0 Wants are shaped by one\'92s society and are described in terms of objects that will satisfy needs.\
For example; an American in Kolkata needs food but wants McDonald\'92s.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b\fs36 \cf0 Demands \'96 Human wants that are backed by buying power\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sa300\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs27 \cf0 Given their wants and resources, people demand products with benefits that add up to the most va^ue and satisfaction.\
