\f5 \cf5 A business will use a range of promotional activities for its product, depending on the\'a0
\b marketing strategy
\b0 \'a0and the\'a0
\b budget
\b0 \'a0available.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sb100\sa100\partightenfactor0
\cf5 The way in which promotion is targeted is split into two types:\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\b \cf5 Above the line promotion
\b0 \'a0\'96 paid for communication in the independent media e.g. advertising on TV or in the newspapers. Though it can be targeted, it could be seen by anyone outside the target audience.\

\b Below the line promotion
\b0 \'a0\'96 promotional activities where the business has direct control e.g. direct mailing and money off coupons. It is aimed directly at the target audience.\
\pard\pardeftab720\fi720\ri0\sl276\slmult1\sa200\partightenfactor0

