\b \cf13 \ul \ulc13 Introduction to Marketing Mix
\b0 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\qj\partightenfactor0

\b \cf13 Marketing
\b0 \'a0is the process of identifying, anticipating, and satisfying customers' requirements with the purpose to make profits. In this process marketing managers and marketing representatives have to take various marketing decisions to make the operations profitable. They have to decide what combination of marketing policies and procedures be adopted to bring about desired behaviour of trade and consumers at minimum cost. They have to decide how can advertising, personal selling, pricing, packaging, channels, warehousing, and the other elements of marketing be manipulated and mixed to make marketing operations profitable. More specifically, they have to decide a marketing mix - a decision making method in relation with\'a0the product, price, promotion, and distribution.\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\partightenfactor0
\cf13 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf13 The term Marketing Mix was introduced by\'a0
\b Neil H. Borden
\b0 \'a0in his article - "
\b The Concept of Marketing Mix
\b0 ". He learned about it in a research bulletin on the management of marketing costs, written by his associate,\'a0
\b Prof. James Culliton
\b0 . in 1948. In this study of manufacturers' marketing costs he described the business executive as a "decider," an "artist" - a "
\b mixer of ingredients
\b0 ," who sometimes follows a recipe prepared by others, sometimes prepares his own recipe as he goes along, sometimes adapts a recipe to the ingredients immediately available, and sometimes experiments with or invents ingredients no one else has tried.\'a0\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\partightenfactor0
\cf13 \
\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\qj\partightenfactor0

\b \cf13 \ul \ulc13 Definition of Marketing Mix
\b0 \ulnone \
According to
\b \'a0Philip Kotler
\b0 \'a0-\'a0
\i "
\b Marketing Mix
\b0 \'a0is the combination of four elements, called the 4P's (product, Price, Promotion, and Place), that every company has the option of adding, subtracting, or modifying in order to create a desired marketing strategy"
\i0 \
\
According to\'a0
\b Principles of Marketing, 14e, Kotler and Armstrong, 2012
\b0 \'a0-\'a0
\i "
\b The Marketing Mix
\b0 \'a0is the set of tactical marketing tools - Product, Price, Promotion, and Place - that the firm blends to produce the response it wants in the target market."
\i0 \
\

\b \ul Meaning of Marketing Mix
\b0 \ulnone \
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\sa240\qj\partightenfactor0
\cf13 The Marketing Mix is a marketing tool used by marketing professionals. It is often crucial when determining product or brand's offering, and it is also called as 4P's (Product, Price, Promotion, and Place) of marketing. \'a0However, in case of services of different nature the 4 P's have been expanded to 7P's or 8P's.\uc0\u8232 \u8232 In recent times, giving more importance to customer a new concept have been introduced, i.e.\'a0
\b Concept of 4C's
\b0 . The Concept of 4C's is more customer-driven replacement of 4P's. According to Lauterborn's the 4C's are - Consumer, Cost, Communication, and\'a0Convenience. According to Shimizu's the 4C's are \'a0-Commodity, Cost, Communication, and Channel.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\sl384\qj\partightenfactor0

\b \cf13 4P's - Producer-oriented Model of Marketing Mix
\b0 \
\pard\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-360\ri0\sl384\sb100\sa100\partightenfactor0
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\fs20 \cf13 \'a5	
\f0\b\fs23 Product
\b0 \'a0- Products are offerings that a marketer offers to the target audience to satisfy their needs and wants. Product can be tangible good or intangible service. Tangible products are goods like - cellphone, television, or motor car, whereas intangible products are services like - financial service in a bank, health\'a0treatment\'a0by a doctor, legal advice of a lawyer.\'a0\
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\fs20 \'a5	
\f0\b\fs23 Price
\b0 \'a0- Price is the amount that is charged by marketer of his offerings or the amount that is paid by consumer for the use or consumption of the product. Price is crucial in determining the organization's profit and survival. Adjustments in price affects the demand and sales of the product. Marketers are required to be aware of the customer perceived value of the product to set the right price.\'a0\
\ls15\ilvl0
\f6\fs20 \'a5	
\f0\b\fs23 Promotion
\b0 \'a0- Promotion represents the different methods of communication that are used by marketer to inform target audience about the product. promotion includes - advertising, personal selling, public relation, and sales promotion.\'a0\
\ls15\ilvl0
