What is Marketing Intelligence?\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Marketing intelligence is the practice of gathering data relevant to the marketing efforts of an organization, then analyzing that data to accurately and efficiently guide the decision-making process of campaigns. \'a0While marketing intelligence is used to assist a number of different marketing goals, at a high level, it\'92s used to inform decisions in relationship to competitors, products and consumer trends or behaviors.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs60 \cf15 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw4
The 4 Sides to Marketing Intelligence\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Marketing intelligence provides organizations with several distinct opportunities to accurately navigate the complexities of the marketing landscape that are unique to the organization. When done correctly, there are four sides that help marketers formulate successful strategic decisions:\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
1. Competitive Advantage\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
This form of marketing intelligence involves collecting data from competitors in order to distill insights that can be used to more effectively develop business strategies. By understanding which consumers choose competitors and why, brands can better align marketing efforts to shift products and messaging toward the ideal consumers.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
2.\'a0Product Intelligence\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
Product intelligence involves taking a deep dive into the brand\'92s products as well as how those products stack up within the market. Typically done by speaking to consumers, polling\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.marketingevolution.com/marketing-essentials/target-audience?hsLang=en%22%20%5Ct%20%22_blank"}}{\fldrslt \cf16 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
target audiences}}\'a0or engaging them with surveys, organizations can better understand the differentiators and competitive advantages of their products. From there, teams can better align products to the unique consumer interests and problems that help drive conversions.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs48 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
3.\'a0Marketing Understanding\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

\fs26 \cf0 \kerning1\expnd1\expndtw6
The data used for this variant of marketing intelligence revolves around examining the marketplaces populated by customers or prospects. Are there magazines, books or industry journals the marketplace reads? Or perhaps organizations they are a part of? Understanding the areas where your target audiences are most active can help you identify the right media mix, the touchpoints and channels to use and where your products can fit into those elements.\
\pard\pardeftab720\ri0\partightenfactor0

